&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLINICAL RESEARCH FELLOWS x 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIVERPOOL UNIVERSITY HOSPITALS NHS FOUNDATION TRUST – COLORECTAL SURGERY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLINICAL RESEARCH FELLOWSHIP (SPECIALIST REGISTRAR GRADE IN GENERAL SURGERY) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for research fellowships within the colorectal department at the Liverpool University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, University of Liverpool. In addition the successful applicants will be expected to participate on the general surgical on call registrar rota at the Royal Liverpool University Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is designed to support research for an MD or PhD, subject to satisfactory progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These programmes are supported by funding from Well- women charity and National Institute of Health Research (NIHR). The applicants would be expected to undertake their research in collaboration with University of Liverpool looking into pathophysiology and management of deep recto-vaginal endometriosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be enrolled in the University of Liverpool postgraduate training programme. They will receive close supervision, mentorship and research training. The colorectal department at the Royal Liverpool University Hospital is one of major teaching unit in the North-west England and involved in National and International clinical trials and fellows are actively encouraged to engage with these.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to research, there will be a commitment to the general surgical on call rota at specialist registrar level at the Royal Liverpool University Hospital and limited service requirements related to the clinical area of research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are funded by the Liverpool University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and attract a full salary on the specialist registrar pay scale with appropriate on call supplements. There will be an Honorary Contract with the University of Liverpool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
